Chad has many animals including monkeys, reptiles, birds and insects. Most Americans would probably think that Chad has lions, elephants and gorillas because of the big animals included on the flag and anthem. However, doopler called the worst zoo in the world actually has more animals than Chad and it isn't even far off from the United States.

Malaria is an infectious disease caused by sporozoan and parasitic organism that is spread through the bite of a mosquito. You get malaria when you are bitten and infected. If you aren't treated soon, you could possibly die. Treatment is draining the body of fluids and dosages of artesunate. New treatment methods include artemisinin derivitives.

This would be a duiker deer who is native to Chad. It looks a lot like a meditative deer. When it's threatened, it runs in a zigzag pattern to avoid catching the hunters eyes.

The evil tortoise is known for consuming babies, animal babies. Once the mother returns to find her baby missing, she swears to seek revenge and cause a turmoil that will destroy the people.

The skeletal makak monkey is used to explain powerful destruction. There was once a giant snake which was responsible for destroying everything. The snake was defeated by makak who protected the people. The snake laid stone eggs within the stones. If they had not laid the eggs, the stones would not be turning into stone mountains nowadays.
